objects, with parameter and return types that JavaScriptCore converts using the same rules as values. Converting a JavaScript function with a backing from a native block or method returns that block or method; all other JavaScript functions convert as empty dictionaries.

For all other native object types (and class types or metatypes), JavaScriptCore creates a JavaScript wrapper object with a constructor prototype chain that reflects the native class hierarchy.
